  "prompt": "Why does the Justin Bieber video Baby have more dislikes than likes?",
  "response": "The Justin Bieber music video \"Baby\" became one of the most disliked videos on YouTube for several reasons:\n\n1. **Mass Popularity and Visibility**: The song's widespread appeal and popularity made it a target for internet users who enjoy trolling or expressing disdain for mainstream pop music. Its high visibility naturally attracted more attention, including negative reactions.\n\n2. **Musical Style**: The song's pop and teenage-oriented style might not resonate with all audiences, particularly older demographics or those who prefer different musical genres. Some people criticized it for being formulaic or too commercial.\n\n3. **Viral Trend**: During the time when \"Baby\" was at its peak, disliking the video became a sort of viral trend or meme. People would dislike the video just to be part of the trend or joke, regardless of their actual opinion on the song.\n\n4. **Justin Bieber's Public Image**: Early in his career, Justin Bieber had a polarizing public image. Some individuals disliked him due to his immense success at a young age, his behavior, or the intense fan culture surrounding him.\n\n5. **Internet Culture**: Disliking or criticizing popular content can often be a part of internet culture, where users seek to counterbalance enthusiasm with skepticism or negativity, sometimes exaggerating their reactions for comedic effect.\n\nIt's important to note that YouTube has since changed its display policy, hiding the public dislike count but retaining it for creators' use, so this specific metric is no longer visible to the public.",
